==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''[[curriculum]]'', "course", derived from ''currere'', "to race", + ''vitae'' genitive of ''[[vita#Latin|vita]]'', "life".

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/kəˈrikjuləm ˈviːtai/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[curriculum]] [[vitae]]|curricula vitae}}

# {{UK}} A written account of one's life comprising one's [[education]], [[accomplishment]]s, [[work]] [[experience]], [[publication]]s, etc.; especially, one used to apply for a [[job]].  ''Abbreviation:'' '''[[CV]]'''

====Synonyms====
*[[CV]]
*[[resumé]], [[résumé]]  ''US''

====Translations====
*German: [[Lebenslauf]] {{m}}
*[[Esperanto]]: [[Vivpriskribo]].

